                <witness corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/GAS80">Manuscript Gāsǝč̣čā 18, photographed by Marie-Laure Derat. This is identified by the monks as the personal work of 
                   <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4709Giyorgis">Giyorgis of Saglā</persName> and seems to be very close to or identical with <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3575Mashaf">Maṣḥafa saʿātāt element TEI with id LIT3575Mashaf</ref>.</witness>
                <witness corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFet9#3">Belongs probably to <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3575Mashaf">Maṣḥafa saʿātāt element TEI with id LIT3575Mashaf</ref>.</witness>
                <witness cert="low" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFet12">Belongs probably to <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3575Mashaf">Maṣḥafa saʿātāt element TEI with id LIT3575Mashaf</ref>, see an invocation for king <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>.</witness>
                <witness type="external" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML4016">Seems to be a hybrid of <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2230Saatat">Saʿātāt za-gǝbṣ</ref> and <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3575Mashaf">Maṣḥafa saʿātāt element TEI with id LIT3575Mashaf</ref>.</witness>
                <witness corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFet381">Seems to be a hybrid of <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2230Saatat">Saʿātāt za-gǝbṣ</ref> and <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3575Mashaf">Maṣḥafa saʿātāt element TEI with id LIT3575Mashaf</ref>.</witness>
